cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about building a language model for text with named entities, which is a common problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach to building the model, which involves leveraging entity type information, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the model on two benchmark datasets, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
